# Cisco SG500 / SG500XG stacks to auto-renew HTTPS cert for.
# One FQDN per line. Blank lines and #-comments are ignored.
#
# The FQDN must:
#   - Resolve (public or internal DNS) so acme.sh's DNS-01 challenge can target
#     the correct zone on Cloudflare.
#   - Point at the switch's mgmt IP (since the renewer probes :443 for the
#     pre-check — use an --ip override in code if the FQDN is not routable).
#
# SSH access details are set via env (not per-host):
#   SG500_SSH_USER  (default: claude)
#   SG500_SSH_KEY   (default: /config/ssh/sg500-key, mount from ./config/ssh/)
#   SG500_SLOT      (default: 2 — SG500 has only slots 1 and 2)
#
# Example:
# sw-core.int.example.com
# sw-dmz.int.example.com
